  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries and is considered a serious financial crime. Specifically:\n\n1. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems.\n\n2. It is a criminal offense in most jurisdictions worldwide, with significant legal penalties including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional sanctions\n\n3. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations designed to detect and prevent such activities.\n\n4. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to establish global standards for combating money laundering.\n\nMoney laundering is a direct contravention of legal standards and financial regulations, representing a serious criminal offense with substantial legal consequences.",
